You can use the `justify-content: flex-end;` property in CSS to align a row of divs to the right when using Flexbox. Here's an example:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.item {
  /* add your styles here */
}
```

And here's an HTML example that uses the above CSS:
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="item">Item 1</div>
  <div class="item">Item 2</div>
  <div class="item">Item 3</div>
</div>
```

In this example, the `.container` div is set to be a Flex container with `display: flex;`, and the items are aligned to the right using `justify-content: flex-end;`.
